# Getting Started with PalJS

## Prerequisites
To get started with PalJS, you need:
- Git - <https://git-scm.com>
- Node.js >=12 - <https://nodejs.org>
- Package manager (npm, yarn, pnpm)
- Prisma CLI - <https://www.prisma.io/docs/reference/tools-and-interfaces/prisma-cli/installation>

## Installation
Install the PalJS CLI globally:
```bash
npm install -g @paljs/cli
# or
yarn global add @paljs/cli
```

## Project Creation
Use the CLI to create a new project:
```bash
npx @paljs/cli create
```

The CLI offers several starter templates:
- full-stack-nextjs
- full-stack-gatsbyjs
- apollo-nexus-schema
- apollo-sdl-first
- graphql-modules

## UI Frameworks
PalJS supports multiple UI frameworks:
- Material UI
- Material UI + PrismaAdmin UI
- Tailwind CSS
- Tailwind CSS + PrismaAdmin UI

For more information, refer to the [README.md](mdc:README.md).
